\.TH GTEATIME 1 "May 2026" "gteatime 1.0.2" "User Commands"

.SH NAME
gteatime \- lightweight GTK3 system-tray tea and coffee timer
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B gteatime
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B gteatime
is a small GTK 3 desktop timer for tea and coffee presets inspired by
.I kteatime.
It runs as a tray application and tries to use
.I StatusNotifierItem
over D-Bus when available, falling back to the
.I XEmbed
system tray protocol on X11.
.PP
Left click on the tray icon opens the configuration window.  Right click
opens the preset menu.  Closing the window hides it while the
application continues to run in the tray.
.PP
When a timer is active, the tray tooltip shows the remaining time.
When the timer finishes, a desktop notification is shown.
.SH OPTIONS
This program currently has no command-line options.
.SH FILES
.TP
.I /usr/bin/gteatime
Program executable.
.TP
.I /usr/share/applications/gteatime.desktop
Desktop entry.
.TP
.I /usr/share/icons/hicolor/scalable/apps/gteatime.svg
Main application icon.
.TP
.I /usr/share/icons/hicolor/scalable/apps/gteatime-on.svg
Systray icon when timer is on.
.TP
.I /usr/share/icons/hicolor/scalable/apps/gteatime-off.svg
Systray icon when timer is off.
.SH REQUIREMENTS
The desktop environment must provide either a
.I StatusNotifierItem
watcher or an X11 system tray manager.
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR kteatime (1)
